snippet.textDisplay:
OMG!! ... This got so serious, so fast .. I honestly stopped laughing after the 1st bleach fail. They should regulate this stuff & only be able to be sold to qualified hair technicians!!
Stop ruining your hair, if you are going to attempt to home bleach your hair, at least do some research about it first. See how much lighter your hair could go before it starts falling out in massive chunks like this poor girl. I'm guessing she'll never do a home bleach ever again. Not only was that a very costly experience, but it must have taken it's toll on her mental well being too. I can imagine her sitting alone in her bedroom & having a few tears, even if she never admitted it. I did the same thing when my mother took me to the salon & chopped my lovely long hair into a short bob, as I kept complaining about her hurting me when she was brushing. Permanently scarred. Seems silly, but it's only thing that I've ever loved about myself. Lets hope she learns from her mistakes & also teaches her friends not to follow!!!!

snippet.textDisplay: Excuse typos, I messaged you on Instagram and just copied and pasted. My ig is @shrewsie_     Hi brad!! I’m a huuuuuuge fan. I just recently watched your latest bleach fail video, and lmaoooooo your commentary always brightens my day. I love how funny, real, and how NEW YORK YOU ARE!!! Lol Anywho, I hope you see this I wanted to enter to win those beauty experience tickets your giving away First and foremost my name is Christina, I’m from the boogie down Bronx and I live with my mom. I would want to take my mom with me. She and LOVEEE All things beauty. It’s one of the many reasons she and I are so close. She taught me all I know about beauty, hair, makeup, skincare. To this day, and I’m 22 she’s 45, she continues to teach me Now my mom went to empire beauty school. Her dream was to open her own salon Unfortunately those dreams were dashed and divided because she was in a car accident loses almost 100% usage of her right hand, her dominant hand. This was heart breaking to say the least. My strong mother was now weak and I could see how it affected her For some time I had to help her blow her hair out until she grew enough strength to try to do it herself. Her entire wrist was shattered, she has a screen that will forever be in her hand. She cannot bend her wrist, it’s forever in a straight position, ligaments were torn, and she has little feeling in some fingers. My dream is to one day be able to give back to her the way she truly deserves. My mom is THE most giving, loving, caring, strongest, selfless person in the whole world. And even if I could surprise her with these tickets and have her meet you, would be AMAZING. And I know it would bring her joy as she’s ALWAAAAYS begged me to go to the beauty experience expo with her when she was in beauty school and the timing was just never right. She’s so beautiful and my whole world. When my dad died she took over in ways that some would seem impossible. She truly is Wonder Woman!! She always supported all my dreams and when I was a super active club kid and burlesque dancer, she would come out with me to places like Susan bartsch’s parties, Kayvon Zand’s parties, the box, house of yes, etc 😹 she was always there supporting the glamour of it all So I hope you see this message and I hope to bring my mom to the beauty experience and meet you!!!

My dream is to one day be able to give back to her the way she truly deserves. My mom is THE most giving, loving, caring, strongest, selfless person in the whole world. And even if I could surprise her with these tickets and have her meet you, would be AMAZING. And I know it would bring her joy as she’s ALWAAAAYS begged me to go to the beauty experience expo with her when she was in beauty school and the timing was just never right. She’s so beautiful and my whole world. When my dad died she took over in ways that some would seem impossible. She truly is Wonder Woman!! She always supported all my dreams and when I was a super active club kid and burlesque dancer, she would come out with me to places like Susan bartsch’s parties, Kayvon Zand’s parties, the box, house of yes, etc 😹 she was always there supporting the glamour of it all So I hope you see this message and I hope to bring my mom to the beauty experience and meet you!!!

snippet.textDisplay: This is why I'm so scared to do my hair myself 😱 I've always done my hair in a salon (unless I'm just straightening it with a flat iron), when I decided to go an unnatural color I did what I always do, go to a professional. Well I paid almost $400 to have an ombre green, I'm realistic and have no expectations of pastel colors from my dark ass hair, but my stylist insisted she could do it and I believed her since she's the pro. It took her 10 hours to bleach (just once), wash, dye and style my hair. 10 fucking hours. When I called I explained I'm Hispanic and have super thick hair AND a ton of it and she insisted she knew how to handle my type of hair. Well when I went to the register to pay I ended up bawling because I looked like a Dalmatian. I had brown, orange, green and darker green spots eeeeeeverywhere. The receptionist felt so bad she got the manager and demanded in my behalf that I get a refund. I got the refund and then went to another salon that ended up dying my hair a dark green, like I wanted, to cover the spots, but because my hair is so thick they ended up having two salon artists on me, one blow drying one half of my hair and the other side done by the second artist. I felt pressured into tipping two artists and really bad that my type of hair apparently needed to be "man handled". Got tired of green eventually and went blue but they gave me a suuuuuuuper dark blue, I hated it. I waited for it to fade and dyed my hair myself (profile pic) and was very happy with it! But then I got a job that didn't allow unnatural hair colors so I headed off to yet another salon to get it back to natural color and they dyed it brown twice and it was horrible so they ended up using box dye black (I saw the box they were using). So basically every damn salon I've been to has been a horrible experience. But I'm too scared to bleach it myself :(

snippet.textDisplay: Not gonna lie, I made some of those fuck-ups bleaching at home (bleaching twice on the same week, combing with bleacher on, trying to fix stains and not really fixing them), or bleaching already fragile hair to try to remove fantasy color to apply another and all, but not to THIS point. Moreover, if something went wrong (and it did, more than once), it was my fault and my fault only. I would never put a friend in the horrible position of "hey, you do my hair and if I end up bald, it's your doing". I had a friend help me once, but it was just because I couldn't properly access the back of my head and I had used the same product before and knew exactly what to do, and kept checking with a mirror. And of course, I would never bleach someone else's hair. I would gladly help to dye already lightened hair, but would NEVER use a product I have no idea how it works or how it reacts on her hair. I can only speak for my own, after all.
